    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>What a Teacher Needs</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Letter from Randi Weingarten, president of United Federation of Teachers, says effective teachers need smaller class sizes and safe, supportive environment (Jan 19 Tom Moore Op-Ed article)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Bravo to Tom Moore for ''Classroom Distinctions'' (Op-Ed, Jan. 19)!</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Bravo to Tom Moore for ''Classroom Distinctions'' (Op-Ed, Jan. 19)!</p>
        <p>Sainthood and martyrdom should not be prerequisites for successful teaching in high-poverty schools. While many teachers qualify on both counts, that is not the sine qua non for making a difference in a child's life.</p>
        <p>Effective teachers will tell you they need smaller class sizes and a safe, adequately staffed, supportive environment where they are treated as professionals and asked for input.</p>
        <p>That's what we fight for every day; and it's the least we can do to help our teachers help our students.</p>
        <p>Randi Weingarten  President  United Federation of Teachers  New York, Jan. 22, 2007</p>
      </block>
